          "type": "theory",
          "data": {
            "title": "Why Khmer looks like chaos (but it's not)",
            "text": "In Khmer, there are no spaces between words.\n\nSo the text looks like this:\n\n·ûõ·û∂·ûà·û∂·ûì·ûÜ·û∂·ûî·üã·ûõ·ûø·ûÑ·ûö·û†·ûº·ûè·ûä·ûõ·üã·ûê·üí·ûÑ·üÉ\n\nCompletely unreadable, right?\n\n(This is completely normal. You're not broken.)\n\nBut here's the secret: Inside this chaos is a strict structure.\n\nThink of it like:\n- A skeleton (consonant) = the main part\n- Everything else = decorations hanging on the skeleton\n\nOnce you know the skeleton, the whole thing becomes readable.",
            "sublesson_title": "Orientation & Foundation"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "theory",
          "data": {
