          "type": "theory",
          "data": {
            "title": "The Commander Principle: One rule that explains everything",
            "text": "Here's the magic:\n\nThe consonant (the Hero) decides how the vowel will sound.\n\nSame vowel mark.\nDifferent consonant = Different sound.\n\nWhy? Because the consonant is the COMMANDER.\nIt controls the tone.\n\nSun consonant + vowel = vowel sounds CLEAN\nMoon consonant + same vowel = vowel sounds ALTERED (with E or O coloring)",
            "sublesson_title": "Commander Principle"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "quiz",
          "data": {
            "question": "Will they sound the same? Look at: ·ûÄ + ·û∂ (Sun) vs ·ûÇ + ·û∂ (Moon). Same vowel mark, different commander.",
            "options": [
